description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and dynamic nurse to join our hospital Supportive and Palliative Care Team. The successful candidate will join the team in the provision of specialist advice and support to improve the quality of life for patients with malignant or non-malignant life-limiting diseases. This includes the support of patients undergoing CAR-T therapy, a new ground breaking treatment available at University Hospitals Bristol and Weston .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have previous recent palliative care experience, excellent communication skills, can work autonomously and as part of a multidisciplinary team we want to hear from you. The post holder will have the responsibility of line management and will act as a resource to the wider team. In addition to providing in depth specialist knowledge and advice they will be expected to participate across the teams activities in areas of education, audit and service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strongly advise contacting the team to discuss further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Date of interview 16th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlie Beard - Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01173423507&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
